            <bug_when>2009-09-23 12:14:17 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Currently  the HtmlArea does allow to insert hyperlinks even if no text is selected. If that&#39;s the case the URL of the link to insert is used as text content.

Naturally the browsers do not support creating a link without a valid text selection. To support this feature anyway the link is inserted manually. This manual insert is causing problems for Gecko browsers when trying to undo /  redo the creation of the hyperlink.

Re-evaluate the feature of creating a hyperlink without a valid  text selection.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
